page.title: 14ECOLOGY IN KINGS NORTON
page.content: On Monday Third {June 1985} we went to the Kings Norton canal for the Domesday topic to see things about ecology and the landscape.The first thing we saw was a frog.It was dark green.On the trees there was a lot of blossom.There was also a lot of rubbish like sweet papers and big black bags.We saw a lot of plant life too.We saw an old mooring lock where the old barges used to go before it got knocked down beca- use of {vandalism}.The fish lived in polluted water and as mentioned there was loads of litter.The banks were mostly washed away and old moorings were standing in the canal.The name of some of the boats on the canal were Norman,Shark,Rellever,Kerie.Calipso 3 and Cover,Heath.There is a compound for Patrick Motors cars.There was also plants growing in a brick wall. By the children of Broadmeadow J/I.
